reviews_data.review_text: Came this morning around 8:05 am and the doors were still locked with the lights out. They are supposed to open at 8am. When we finally got in around 8:15, nothing was prepared. We ordered a ham and cheese pasty and it was stale. My latte was good though.

Really poor/ cheap choices in the alternative milks with lots of additives and chemicals instead of something  more authentic and conscious. Poor taste and quality for this alone- as the coffee is great but the fake coconut milk and additives are horrible
Visited with a friend and it was a cute and nice atmosphere. Not many vegan or vegetarian options, but I enjoyed it.

Sumaq Coffee in Charlotte is a vibrant café with a cozy, artistic vibe and a strong cultural identity. The space is beautifully decorated, with indoor and outdoor seating that’s perfect for relaxing or working. Their coffee is excellent, especially the Sumaq Latte, and the menu includes flavorful sandwiches, empanadas, and pastries made in-house with fresh ingredients.
Kind of a hidden gem. Great sandwiches and wraps. The lattes are excellent and well balanced
I ❤️ it
Overall experience is pleasant. Food was good, but the cake did not seem fresh. The place was spacious with a lot of seating. I wish the place was open later, specially on weekends.

Sumaq is a Peruvian coffee shop with delicious food and drinks. I got an iced oat milk Sumaq latte. It was very yummy with a cinnamon sweetness to it. I also ordered the Chicken Walpa Wrap and it was delicious. Very flavorful and not spicy. We also ordered the breakfast flatbread which was a good size and yummy, especially the bread. We went back for some small seconds with a pastry and an empanada. Both were very yummy!
The space is fantastic! It has a chill vibe and has a very large second space with lots of seating. Service at Sumaq is very straightforward, they are efficient but not fawning on you.

I really liked the cozy vibe of this place and the coffee was great.
Unfortunately, my experience was spoiled by the food. When I ordered a carrot cake, I noticed there was only one piece left in the display. I specifically asked the person at the counter if they had fresh ones. They went inside, brought out fresh slices, but still put the old one into my box. It was very stale and hard to eat. This is disappointing especially after I checked beforehand if it was fresh.

I hope they pay more attention to quality and honesty, because the atmosphere and coffee deserve better.
Great spot with delicious coffee and an amazing  maracuya cheesecake! I highly recommend visiting this place!

This is probably one of the best coffee shops I’ve been to…the environment, the cleanliness (cleaning after every table), the modern look, the quietness, and most importantly the energy behind it were all fantastic. Food was made super quickly, the cashier was awesome helping us choose from some of her recommended options. Food presentation was a big shocker basically on par with a luxury fine dine in downtown haha, amazing experience.

We drove from north Charlotte to try Sumaq Coffee and overall were happy with our experience! Not impressed enough to make the drive again any time soon, but the venue itself was very clean, modern, and spacious. The Sumaq Latte was pretty good, but the Iced Americano was very watered down and didn’t even taste like it was made with espresso. The Sumaq Waffle was great and we paired it with the guava jam which was good, but too strong of a flavor and covered the light cheesiness of the waffle. The Egg Salad Croissant was good as well.

The space is open and inviting — perfect for working or catching up with friends. I tried their wrap; it was okay, nothing special, but the coffee definitely makes up for it. Worth visiting if you’re in the area.

Sumaq Coffee offers an authentic coffee experience with a rich, flavorful taste that really stands out. You can tell they take pride in sourcing and preparing their coffee — every sip feels fresh and well-crafted.

The ambience is warm, inviting, and perfect for relaxing with a book, catching up with friends, or just enjoying some quiet time. It has that cozy, welcoming vibe that makes you want to linger.

If you’re a coffee lover, this is definitely a spot you’ll appreciate. Highly recommended for anyone who values both quality coffee and a great atmosphere.
Everything was delicious.
The customer service was super sweet and kind.  Also, the food was so delicious 10/10 ✨
I always come here on my days off — it’s so peaceful. I love the environment, and the customer service is always excellent! 😍
Great place I ❤️
There’s nothing like a fresh cup of coffee to awaken and refresh the mind. This brew was smooth, bold, and easily one of the most enjoyable cups I’ve had."
Great coffee and food. Very friendly service with a nice relaxing atmosphere
I have a feeling their cakes have been sitting out for days. I ordered two cakes and both had strawberries on them. Both strawberries were not fresh, very dry, I didn't eat it.

This place is perfect for breakfast! The croissant and the meat wrap were super tasty.

I wouldn’t recommend the coffee, but I’ll definitely be coming back! ☀️🥐🥙

Best coffee place in Charlotte!
Friendly staff, food is so tasty and fresh. Coffee is delicious! My favorite is the Sumaq Latte, both iced and hot.
I absolutely love coming here. It’s one of my favorite spots to go for a snack and matcha. Their empanadas are incredible.
Great coffee shop with plenty of options.
The food was delicious.

Tried waffles and caramel latte. Waffles were great in taste, but too thick. The guava syrup was absolutely delicious. Caramel latte was okay, It had  chocolate notes which was a bit unexpected. This shop was absolutely beautiful and service was excellent!!!
Absolutely delicious selection of coffees and plenty of seating. I enjoy places like this that have real mugs for dine-in customers.

La verdad habia escuchado bastante de este negocio fui a probar el cafe y me decepciono, el cafe sabia solo a cafe artificial, parecia que no era ni fuerte. No me parecio un cafe natural, no estaba bueno. lastima porque el lugar es lindo y la atencion muy buena pero la calidad del cafe no la recomiendo.

Place is big. Great for studying. Parking a bit tedious. Food was ok. Matcha was missing the matcha part of it, it was more like green milk. Dessert was eh. But atmosphere was good, friendly staff as well. Plenty of seating around.
Stopped here by chance after Costco and its our new favorite. Great atmosphere and amazing cappuccinos.
Love the coffee, food and the whole vibe of this coffee shop. It's close to Jeff Adam's park, so best place to go too, after a good tennis practice.

My first time discovering Sumaq Coffee. My family was shopping nearby, and I just wanted a cool place for some hot coffee. It was early on a very hot afternoon in July, so no one was outside, but there was otherwise welcoming seating out front. The interior was bright and clean, with both individuals and groups meeting and talking in the spacious seating area with high, industrial style ceilings.
My medium Americano was priced below most specialty coffee shops, prepared quickly, and was perfectly hot.
Very friendly staff.
It was good to see such a successful, locally run shop on South Blvd.
From my first experience, I would recommend it, and I will return.

It was around 9:45 AM on a Tuesday morning. I went there for a coffee and a small snack. After entering, I felt very nice about the place and the modern bright atmosphere. But when I reached the counter, I lost my enthusiasm. The staff were so dull and not very welcoming; it was like, "Yeah! You pay and we serve... that's all there is to it."

I ordered a hot latte and a plain butter croissant, both costing around $10+. The coffee was pretty below average with no flavor. I was not able to finish the medium coffee and ended up dumping some. The croissant was almost like a Hawaiian bun, with no layers, butter, and the inside was doughy (check the picture). It was one of the worst croissants I've ever had.

I have no interest in going back anytime in the future. They really need to change a lot in their preparation. It's not the facility and ambiance that brings customers back; it's always the food and drink. I'm still wondering about the 4.6 rating on Google that made me come here.
Dominica and the entire crew are great! The best coffee and great food, and a beautiful place to work or unwind
For atmosphere and coffee it's good.. Food is frankly below average and not worth the price I have tried three items, all of them are below average..

reviews_data.review_text: Sumaq Coffee is a gem. The coffee was rich and delicious, but the real prize was the chicken empanada, flavorful, and worth the visit on its own. The space is beautifully decorated and has the kind of atmosphere that makes it easy to settle in and get work done. Parking can be a little tricky, so plan ahead if you’re driving. I’ll definitely be back for another empanada (or two).

#1 COFFEE IN CHARLOTTE
Amazing coffee (must try Sumaq syrup)
All the deserts r to die for

Also love that they have live music every now and then, definitely check them out

Sumaq is a hidden gem on South Blvd, every dish I’ve tried has been full of flavor and cooked to perfection. The ingredients are fresh, the portions are generous, and the staff is friendly and welcoming. It’s clear they take pride in what they serve.

That said, be prepared for a bit of a wait. There’s often a line, especially during peak hours, and food can take a while to come out. But honestly, it’s worth it. The line just proves how popular and loved this spot is.

If you’re in no rush and want to enjoy a truly satisfying meal, Sumaq is 100% worth the visit. I’ll definitely keep coming back!
Great place for a coffee

If your ever near here you should stop in the people that work here are all first class with a warm smile and friendly attitude. I've been working in front of their business for weeks they are so friendly they open their doors to us to use their restrooms and never have anything negative to say. In a world full of businesses that don't put people first they are a step above first class act all the way and needless to say the cake and coffee is absolutely AMAZING!!!!
Beautiful, calm and clean. Food and drinks are delicious!
Un lugar muy muy relajante , excelente servicio 👌 todo muy rico 😋

Been wanting to try this place for a while. Very good vibe and nice decor with lots of seating.

Near by area is kinda sus but the place itself is good.

Will definitely come back.
Best lattes I have ever had! We have loved every pastry we have gotten here
The service is very good. The atmosphere is very pleasant and the coffee is excellent.

Cute and modern coffee shop! I was influenced by the Peruvian/South American inspired coffee, and was delighted by the coffee and sweet treats offered. I got a hot sumaq latte that is more savory and rich in flavor and my dad got a hot dulce de leche latte which wasn't too sweet and also rich in flavor. We got an empanada, fig and cheese treat, and dulce de leche cake. Orders came out in a bit and were packaged neatly. The empanada was a bit small for what it's worth. The fig and cheese treat was great and not too sweet which complemented the coffee, and the cake was delicious and paired great with a coffee. The shop is really cute and has an open sitting area with lots of sunlight then one in the back that's more cozy for hanging out. It can be easy to overlook, but the vibes, good flavors, and lots of parking in CLT makes it worth a try.

reviews_data.review_text: Went on Saturday. Super friendly staff and cozy atmosphere. Food was wonderful.
Great place to "park" yourself for a yummy work lunch.  They've expanded the interior so it's even larger now.
Solid cappuccino.  I didn’t have any but the baked goodies looked delicious!

The food is always great no matter what we’ve orders. I always enjoy their protein bowls and my husband has had pasties, empanadas, breakfast flatbread, and more. I usually get their Matcha, which is great. Only downside is they’re often out of their monthly specialty syrups (at least 2 of the 3 times I’ve been recently).

Visiting from out of state and stopped here just for coffee. I ordered an iced latte with strawberry syrup and it was one of the worst coffees I’ve ever had. It was mostly milk and the coffee itself was so bitter it tasted burnt. Really disappointed to have paid around $7 for a coffee that wasn’t drinkable.
I had a coconut refresher and it was very good for a hot summer in June. Cute place!!

The most overrated coffee shop in Charlotte.
This was my second and last time giving Sumaq Caffe a chance. Every visit, there’s always something on the menu they don’t have. The desserts—like their cheesecakes—are stale, and my Nutella waffles were hard as a rock. To top it off, the tables were dirty and the overall vibe was just unpleasant. Never again.
I love this little place! A great spot to go to catch up, grab a bite to eat and/or sip on some great coffee!

Sumaq keeps me coming back for their absolutely delicious strawberry matcha. Their coffee drinks, pastries, and food are all great as well. Very happy to have found this place and highly recommend it. Not to mention, the atmosphere is very inviting.

Edit: as of recent, the matcha latte has dropped in quality. I’ve gotten it twice recently and it has been really subpar both times. We’ve also had to wait a really long time for our food when there were not a lot of people there. Hope this is just a phase!

We came to get coffee and do some studying around 1:30, got our coffee and sat, and not even 20 minutes later the manager is telling us we have to leave and they are closing early for maintenance. They should’ve given customers a courtesy and put a notice on the door or told customers when ordering that they planned to close early. Instead they waited til the very last minute so that they could ensure they got orders in. Such a scammy way to conduct business, we would’ve went somewhere else had we known we could only stay for 20 minutes. The hot coffee was also cold when we got it, I guess they don’t heat their milk/espresso enough. Never coming here again.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Yasmine, we encountered some maintenance issues that necessitate our immediate attention for safety reasons. We sincerely apologize for any inconvenience this may cause. Please know that such situations are beyond our control. We hope you’ll give us another chance to redeem ourselves. Thanks for visiting.

reviews_data.review_text: Excellent !! Spacious with plenty of comfortable seating . Coffee and food was excellent .
Good coffee. Good ambience. Lot of place to sit.

I drove 35 minutes south just to check out Sumac—and I’m so glad I did! The interior is beautiful and inviting, with such a cozy, curated vibe that made it totally worth the trip. The service was genuinely warm and friendly—everyone made me feel welcome right away. I ordered a wrap that I loved, and I also tried an empanada that I thought was chicken (oops), but they kindly clarified it was actually shredded beef—super helpful and kind about it, too! I’ll definitely be back the next time I’m in the area. A charming spot with great food and even better energy!
Yummy latte and super yummy mango cheesecake

Delicious/ warm coffee and breakfast pastries.Love the aesthetic that the place has from the decoration to the plates that they serve you pastries on. Its all so welcoming. Had to come back during lunch time another day and the salad they was so filling. This place is perfect for for an anytime visit

Very simplistic, beautiful decor. Great music, great vibe, went here for a little day date with my hubby on a Wednesday. I had a egg salad croissant which was fat and fresh. He had the super hot ham and cheese bread and we both had drip coffees, which were all fantastic. Pretty little midday stop.

This place is seriously beautiful — I love the aesthetic and the natural, organic design. It feels super cozy, and there are lots of spots to sit, whether you’re meeting up with a friend or trying to get some work done.

That said, the food takes forever. I waited 15 minutes for just one empanada, and it wasn’t even that busy. It’s not the first time either, so just keep that in mind if you’re in a hurry.

Also, the WiFi hasn’t worked either time I’ve been here, which is a bummer if you’re hoping to get stuff done.

Great vibes overall, but definitely not the place if you’re short on time or need reliable internet.

Got my drink size completely wrong. Didn't if I wanted cream, it's 2025 put the cream out were we can use it ourselves. Microwaved my pastry without asking. They give you a discount for using cash but don't have change available. Complete rip off for the quality of service and product offered. If you think this place is great you've never experienced a true coffee shop.

I was really excited to have a breakfast at this place but the experience is super disappointing! The lady who took our order hardly speaks English, I asked for a sandwich and fully cooked egg inside because I’m pregnant (btw their croissant is not real croissant it’s just a bread) and my husband asked for the same, in the end they charged for 2 sandwiches but made just one (we forgot to take the check) so ended up paying extra 10$ for another one. I would say this place is just a hype, yes nice decor and atmosphere overall but the customer service should be better!
Truly one of the best cup of coffees I’ve had in clt

First time trying the place, and will try again in the future. 1st wanted to point out the cashier was super nice and friendly and welcoming on my trip, also i love the ambiance of the place and the light the windows provide. That being said i came here to try this place specifically for the outside patio, which i was very dissapointed in and may be the foundation of this review. The outside area is on the perfect side of the building and has amazinf outdoor furniture and space, that being said none of the egg chairs or patio chairs had cushions making them super uncomfortable to sit in. We found a nice table and chairs out there anyways and went to put up the umbrellas as they were down and we planned to do laptop work and needed a bit of shade on the screens. Let me note that there was no note, no signage, no indication of anything wrong here, i just had simply thought someone had put them down to enjoy the sunlight( i sure was) but much to my suprise the umbrella was super broken, and a string was hanging. No big deal really it was dissapointing but not the end of the world. What made it bad was the man that slowly came out of the building to barrade us about trying to put it up and being rude , we simply stated we didnt know it was broken , he didnt say anything further, but actually walked to another table that was out to tie a rope around it and the really sweet ladies also asked him if their umbrella was out of order, he stated " yes and no matter how many times we tie them up customers take them down" she mentioned maybe putting a sign up. to which he stated, that if they would just not touch it there would be no problem, the ladies were appalled and actually left, we moved inside after the interaction of the rude employee. The man had long hair about shoulder length, a 5 oclock shadow, and a mustach that connected to chin hair, he was wearing a beige hat and button up. Looked to be early 30s late 20s. Managment should really have a talk with him. If he hates the public and his job this much this is not the environment for him. The good in the review was the raspberry sweet tea and the amount of plugs. I would also like to mention maybe getting some back rest cusions on the benches. i did enjoy the sliding butt cushions though. Would give another try but if i walked into this employee again i would leave again. He was very offputting and seemed hostile.

We didn’t expect to have such an amazing lunch here but we did! The matcha is great, the empanadas are delicious, and the sandwiches were excellent. Lots of gluten free options as well. Such an amazing meal!

It is great coffee shop. Very spacious place. I liked empanadas and power bowl with quinoa for breakfast.
Staff is very nice and polite.

Great place for a coffee meeting or bite to eat! The interior has a ton of space for a business meeting or professional coffee date, and the food and drinks are awesome. Get the Sumaq Latte, you'll be glad you did!
Always great service by the staff. Great food and drinks.

My family and I were off to a late start. SUMAQ was out of the way. I told my husband to just get on the interstate we have a long way to drive. Thankfully he said, “Let’s just go.”

SUMAQ was extremely busy on a Sunday morning. The three folks working the register and coffee station were absolute pros. They have a very efficient system; so if you walk in, see a long line, and think about leaving. DO NOT. The line moved quickly and we received our coffee quickly. The food took a bit longer, but it was absolutely worth it. The atmosphere was warm, bright, and inviting. This is definitely a great spot to meet family or friends to chat and eat good food.

When I order a cortado the first thing I notice is the size of the cup it comes in. A cortado is a 1:1 ratio of espresso and steam milk; so when I was handed a petite coffee mug excitement and anticipation rose up in me. I quickly took a few photos then a sip of the cortado. The texture was not as velvety as I would have liked, but the flavor of the espresso was excellent. I immediately grabbed my husband’s dirty chai to taste it. Delicious. Whatever coffee bean SUMAQ is using and the method they are using to brew is magical.

SUMAQ was absolutely worth detour!

Enjoying life one cortado at a time.

reviews_data.review_text: I was traveling in the area and looking for a solid latte. Sumaq came up on Google and it did not disappoint. I had an iced white mocha strawberry latte and it was delicious. Smooth with the perfect amount of sweetness. The server also recommended the beef empanadas. While I don’t tend to gravitate to an empanada, it was truly phenomenal. Crunchy on the outside and warm and soft on the inside. I’ll definitely come back if I’m in the area.

This a very cute establishment, coffee was great, empanadas were fine. However the service was not the best the cashier was not friendly at all. My order was wrong and when i approached the gentleman handling the food, he seemed inconvenienced by it.

walking in here felt like a little oasis. I loved the atmosphere. I liked the deserts a lot and the coffees were great.

reviews_data.review_text: Very noisy atmosphere. The croissant didn't come with butter or cream cheese.

I was SO excited to try this place with my boyfriend. We’re always very careful eating out because he has severe peanut/tree nut allergies. There was a slight language barrier with the woman taking our order, when asking to make sure there isn’t any cross contamination with the foods. Most places accommodate his allergies by leaving a note with the chef, but she refused to ask. She immediately said no. After I asked to speak to the chef, he came out and dryly said everything is prepared on the same surface followed by a careless shrug. It was disappointing that wiping down a counter top and just taking extra precaution for a customer was too much. If that’d be too much we’d completely understand but the lack of warmth and the low tolerance for a short discussion with eager customers was frustrating.
Despite how much I wanted to try this place I felt that I’d rather spend my money in a place that’s more polite and communicative with their customers. Hoping they can improve customer service moving forward.
I got a latte, pastry, & breakfast sandwich, so good! Will definitely be coming back soon!
Fantastic atmosphere with lively energy. Don’t miss the Wallpa Quad sandwich—it’s a must-try! It can get crowded on weekends, but the food is absolutely worth it.
Enjoyed the Sumaq Latte! Nice vibe. Stopped here on my trip in Charlotte.
Relaxing with good coffee ☕️ 😌
Was crowded as hell, had to wait 5 minutes for a table. Do not recommend it during lunch hours. Other than that desserts are delicious 🤤
Best coffee experience in a year!

The place is so cute! i love the aesthetic, super clean and plenty of open indoor seating.
We ordered the Wallpa Quad, Guava and Cheese bread, Wasi House, and the Coconut Guava drink.
The Wallpa Quad was good but the chicken was dry, and the Wasi House sandwich was delicious, but again the chicken was also dry.
I do not recommend the guava and cheese bread, it was super dry and little filling. Coffee was great! Absolutely loved this setting!
Great chill place. Staff was very kind and helpful.  Other than the little turd girl ordering in front of my thinking the world revolved around her, it was fantastic 😂.
Love this place ❤️

The atmosphere is really pretty but unfortunately the coffee is not too well. My iced vanilla latte was extremely watery and the cold foam was very thin. It was obvious that store bought syrup is being used. The waffles they have though, are amazing and worth coming back for. I love the fact that there’s cheese inside but you can barely taste it. Gives it that sweet and salty combo.

We love that we have a local coffee shop here. As we come often, but we feel now it’s losing its appeal. Today, as we ordered our coffee, she was on her cell phone. And paying $15 for coffee we feel the staff shouldn’t be on their cell. She seems like she is new.
Not sure if will keep coming back now. Sucks, seems Charlotte has this issue.

Wonderful place, great food and atmosphere BUT, if the owner doesn’t keep a close eye on things and learns to get the food out the out quicker they’re going to run into problems. As an ex successful restaurant owner, I know these things..
It was okay, I was expecting it to be busy on a Saturday but wow. Waiting 15 minutes for a coffee is alot when they have 3 baristas working. I found it to be over priced and not great.

This place was recommended by so many locals during our vacation and it lived up to the hype. It easily made my top 3 favorite coffee shops. They have mouth watering desserts and parties. Their food was also so delicious. We got their chocolate dulce de leche cake and it was super delicious and almost like a mix of a cake tree leches cake. Their empanadas were super delicious as well and the ham and cheese bread was amazing.

Their Sumaq latte was amazing but what stole the show was the dulce de leche latte, that has to be one of my favorite lattes I’ve ever had. Not overly sweet but you can really taste that dulce de leche taste. An absolute gem and would rate it a 10/10 spot.
Empanadas are amazing
My latte tasted a little burned and my sandwich was underwhelming. Willing to try the place out again and order something different next time. The vibes are 10/10

Nestled on the bustling 6259 South Boulevard in Charlotte, NC, SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is a hidden gem that delights the senses from the moment you step through its doors. This review can’t fully capture the enchanting experience, but I’ll do my best to convey the magic that awaits you at this incredible venue. With an exquisite blend of artisanal coffee, delightful pastries, and exceptional service, SUMAQ stands out as a beacon of culinary artistry and warm hospitality.

Atmosphere & Design: A Contemporary Sanctuary

SUMAQ’s exterior is unassuming yet modern, welcoming visitors into a space that feels both contemporary and cozy. The moment you walk in, you’re greeted by a minimalist yet chic interior, with a tasteful combination of wooden furnishings, industrial accents, and soft lighting that creates a serene and inviting atmosphere. The outdoor patio is an oasis in itself, perfect for a sunny day or a tranquil evening under the stars. The design seamlessly blends comfort with style, making it an ideal spot for everything from a quiet morning coffee to a leisurely afternoon catch-up with friends.

Culinary Delights: A Feast for the Senses

The menu at SUMAQ is a curated selection of culinary delights that showcase a fusion of traditional and innovative flavors. The first thing that caught my eye was the signature iced matcha latte, beautifully layered in a mason jar. The vibrant green matcha contrasted elegantly with the creamy milk, creating a visual treat that was only surpassed by its taste. The matcha was of the highest quality, offering a rich, umami flavor balanced perfectly by the sweetness of the milk. It was a harmonious blend that was both refreshing and indulgent.

Not to be outdone, the iced coffee was equally impressive. Served in a similar mason jar, the coffee had a deep, robust flavor with subtle notes of chocolate and caramel. It was the perfect companion to the delicious pastries I tried next. The flan was a masterpiece, with a silky, smooth texture that melted in your mouth. Topped with a single, vibrant raspberry, it was not just a dessert but a work of art. The caramel sauce was just the right amount of sweet, providing a delightful contrast to the creamy custard.

The alfajor, a traditional South American delight, was another highlight. This delicate pastry, filled with luscious dulce de leche and dusted with powdered sugar, was a bite-sized piece of heaven. It offered a perfect balance of sweetness and texture, with the buttery, crumbly cookie surrounding a rich, caramel-like filling. It’s a treat that evokes the warm, comforting flavors of Latin America, making you feel right at home.

Service: A Touch of Excellence

The service at SUMAQ is in a league of its own, largely thanks to the charismatic and attentive Juan Pablo. His passion for the café and its offerings is evident in every interaction. Juan Pablo’s knowledge of the menu and his genuine enthusiasm make every visit special. He has an uncanny ability to make you feel like the most important guest in the room, offering personalized recommendations and ensuring that every aspect of your experience is perfect. It’s rare to find such a combination of professionalism and warmth, and it’s clear that Juan Pablo and the entire team at SUMAQ take great pride in their work.

A Perfect Conclusion

SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is more than just a café; it’s a destination that promises an unforgettable experience. Whether you’re a local looking for your new favorite spot or a visitor exploring the culinary scene of Charlotte, SUMAQ offers something truly special. The thoughtful design, exceptional food and beverages, and unparalleled service come together to create an experience that’s both sophisticated and heartfelt. I left SUMAQ not only satisfied but inspired, eagerly anticipating my next visit. Thank you, Juan Pablo, and the wonderful team at SUMAQ, for crafting such a memorable experience. This is a five-star gem that deserves every bit of its acclaim!

I also ordered the Chicken Walpa Wrap and it was delicious. Very flavorful and not spicy. We also ordered the breakfast flatbread which was a good size and yummy, especially the bread. I specifically asked the person at the counter if they had fresh ones. They went inside, brought out fresh slices, but still put the old one into my box. It was very stale and hard to eat. I hope they pay more attention to quality and honesty, because the atmosphere and coffee deserve better.
Great spot with delicious coffee and an amazing  maracuya cheesecake! I highly recommend visiting this place!

This is probably one of the best coffee shops I’ve been to…the environment, the cleanliness (cleaning after every table), the modern look, the quietness, and most importantly the energy behind it were all fantastic. Food was made super quickly, the cashier was awesome helping us choose from some of her recommended options. Food presentation was a big shocker basically on par with a luxury fine dine in downtown haha, amazing experience.

The space is open and inviting — perfect for working or catching up with friends. I tried their wrap; it was okay, nothing special, but the coffee definitely makes up for it. Worth visiting if you’re in the area.

Sumaq Coffee offers an authentic coffee experience with a rich, flavorful taste that really stands out. You can tell they take pride in sourcing and preparing their coffee — every sip feels fresh and well-crafted.

The ambience is warm, inviting, and perfect for relaxing with a book, catching up with friends, or just enjoying some quiet time. It has that cozy, welcoming vibe that makes you want to linger.

If you’re a coffee lover, this is definitely a spot you’ll appreciate. Highly recommended for anyone who values both quality coffee and a great atmosphere.
Everything was delicious.

My first time discovering Sumaq Coffee. My family was shopping nearby, and I just wanted a cool place for some hot coffee. It was early on a very hot afternoon in July, so no one was outside, but there was otherwise welcoming seating out front. The interior was bright and clean, with both individuals and groups meeting and talking in the spacious seating area with high, industrial style ceilings.
My medium Americano was priced below most specialty coffee shops, prepared quickly, and was perfectly hot.
Very friendly staff.

From my first experience, I would recommend it, and I will return.

It was around 9:45 AM on a Tuesday morning. I went there for a coffee and a small snack. After entering, I felt very nice about the place and the modern bright atmosphere. But when I reached the counter, I lost my enthusiasm. The staff were so dull and not very welcoming; it was like, "Yeah! You pay and we serve... that's all there is to it."

I ordered a hot latte and a plain butter croissant, both costing around $10+. The coffee was pretty below average with no flavor. I was not able to finish the medium coffee and ended up dumping some. The croissant was almost like a Hawaiian bun, with no layers, butter, and the inside was doughy (check the picture). It was one of the worst croissants I've ever had.

I have no interest in going back anytime in the future. They really need to change a lot in their preparation. It's not the facility and ambiance that brings customers back; it's always the food and drink. I'm still wondering about the 4.6 rating on Google that made me come here.

I was SO excited to try this place with my boyfriend. We’re always very careful eating out because he has severe peanut/tree nut allergies. There was a slight language barrier with the woman taking our order, when asking to make sure there isn’t any cross contamination with the foods. Most places accommodate his allergies by leaving a note with the chef, but she refused to ask. She immediately said no. After I asked to speak to the chef, he came out and dryly said everything is prepared on the same surface followed by a careless shrug. It was disappointing that wiping down a counter top and just taking extra precaution for a customer was too much. Nestled on the bustling 6259 South Boulevard in Charlotte, NC, SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is a hidden gem that delights the senses from the moment you step through its doors. This review can’t fully capture the enchanting experience, but I’ll do my best to convey the magic that awaits you at this incredible venue. With an exquisite blend of artisanal coffee, delightful pastries, and exceptional service, SUMAQ stands out as a beacon of culinary artistry and warm hospitality.

Atmosphere & Design: A Contemporary Sanctuary

SUMAQ’s exterior is unassuming yet modern, welcoming visitors into a space that feels both contemporary and cozy. The moment you walk in, you’re greeted by a minimalist yet chic interior, with a tasteful combination of wooden furnishings, industrial accents, and soft lighting that creates a serene and inviting atmosphere. The outdoor patio is an oasis in itself, perfect for a sunny day or a tranquil evening under the stars. The design seamlessly blends comfort with style, making it an ideal spot for everything from a quiet morning coffee to a leisurely afternoon catch-up with friends.

Culinary Delights: A Feast for the Senses

The menu at SUMAQ is a curated selection of culinary delights that showcase a fusion of traditional and innovative flavors. The first thing that caught my eye was the signature iced matcha latte, beautifully layered in a mason jar. The vibrant green matcha contrasted elegantly with the creamy milk, creating a visual treat that was only surpassed by its taste. The matcha was of the highest quality, offering a rich, umami flavor balanced perfectly by the sweetness of the milk. It was a harmonious blend that was both refreshing and indulgent.

Not to be outdone, the iced coffee was equally impressive. Served in a similar mason jar, the coffee had a deep, robust flavor with subtle notes of chocolate and caramel. It was the perfect companion to the delicious pastries I tried next. The flan was a masterpiece, with a silky, smooth texture that melted in your mouth. Topped with a single, vibrant raspberry, it was not just a dessert but a work of art. The caramel sauce was just the right amount of sweet, providing a delightful contrast to the creamy custard.

The alfajor, a traditional South American delight, was another highlight. This delicate pastry, filled with luscious dulce de leche and dusted with powdered sugar, was a bite-sized piece of heaven. It offered a perfect balance of sweetness and texture, with the buttery, crumbly cookie surrounding a rich, caramel-like filling. It’s a treat that evokes the warm, comforting flavors of Latin America, making you feel right at home.

Service: A Touch of Excellence

The service at SUMAQ is in a league of its own, largely thanks to the charismatic and attentive Juan Pablo. His passion for the café and its offerings is evident in every interaction. Juan Pablo’s knowledge of the menu and his genuine enthusiasm make every visit special. He has an uncanny ability to make you feel like the most important guest in the room, offering personalized recommendations and ensuring that every aspect of your experience is perfect. It’s rare to find such a combination of professionalism and warmth, and it’s clear that Juan Pablo and the entire team at SUMAQ take great pride in their work.

A Perfect Conclusion

SUMAQ Coffee & Catering is more than just a café; it’s a destination that promises an unforgettable experience. Whether you’re a local looking for your new favorite spot or a visitor exploring the culinary scene of Charlotte, SUMAQ offers something truly special. The thoughtful design, exceptional food and beverages, and unparalleled service come together to create an experience that’s both sophisticated and heartfelt. I left SUMAQ not only satisfied but inspired, eagerly anticipating my next visit. Thank you, Juan Pablo, and the wonderful team at SUMAQ, for crafting such a memorable experience. This is a five-star gem that deserves every bit of its acclaim!

Hands down one of the best coffee places in Charlotte. I've been searching for a coffee shop for probably a year now to make a honey lavender oatmeal iced latte and this place nailed it right on the head with the balance of flavor and sweetness. This is my go-to spot now.

I recommend the place, it has several options.
the options with dulce de leche are very delicious.

Sumac is a great cafe with a cozy atmosphere. I went during the winter, but the outdoor patio looks spacious. Everything I tried on the menu was picture perfect and SO delicious! I especially recommend the baked empanadas. If you want some good coffee and chill vibes, this is the place!
